{
  "texts": [
    "The Chains for SQL use a module named SQLDatabase that inspects the schema, tables, columns and foreign keys in the database.",
    "The DDL (Data Definition Language) of the schema is provided at the prompt as context for an LLM in an automated way.",
    "This representation of the schema, illustrated in Figure 4.1, is called Code Representation by Gao et al. (2023).",
    "Using such context in the prompt, the LLM constructs an SQL query for the original NL question, which is then executed and returned by LangChain.",
    "This dissertation proposes to test and evaluate these chains for LangChain's Text-to-SQL task."
  ]
}